<2ND_LINE>AM-ELN--Mspi Senate,0048</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BULLETIN</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GOP Rep. Trent Lott defeated Democratic
Rep. Wayne Dowdy on Tuesday to win the U.S. Senate seat held for 41
years by John C. Stennis, giving the Deep South state two Republican
senators for the first time in this century.
