<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Politics-Quotes     11-08 0314</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Politics-Quotes,280</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, exhorting California supporters on Election eve:
``Don't let them tell you this campaign is over. It won't be over
until the people of California have their say. ... I know this race
is within our grasp both here and across this country.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, at his St. Louis, Mo. campaign headquarters: ``I
feel good, but we're not going to let up until we finish tonight.
... It's in the hands of the gods and the American people.''
   
   DAN QUAYLE, at home in Indiana for his final rally of the
campaign: ``For the last 10 weeks, I've felt like I've been strapped
to the back of an Indy 500 car. But now I can see the checkered
flag, and with your help my friends, George Bush and I will be
seeing you in the winner's circle.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, summing up his vision of the United States at
campaign's end: ``America is not just a place. It's not just a piece
of land or just another country. It's the noblest experiment ever
undertaken on this planet. It's a symbol of what we human beings can
do when we unleash the will of our people, our nation and our
country.''
   
   LLOYD BENTSEN, using lines from a Bruce Springsteen song to sum
up his defiance of discouraging polls: ``No retreat, baby. No
surrender.''
   
   PRESIDENT REAGAN, at his final election rally as president:
``This year my name is not on the ballot. And it won't appear on a
ballot ever again ... unless you count the one that someone up there
casts when your time is done and the moment has arrived for His
verdict, which, when all is said and done, is the only election that
really counts.''
</TEXT>
