<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     11-08 0411</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0421</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Some Areas In Midwest Get First Snows of Season; Rain in Pacific
Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain fell on Election Day today in the Pacific Northwest and Ohio
Valley after snow settled on Sections of the West and Midwest, in
some places for the first time this season.
   Boise, Idaho, got its first flakes, a half inch of snow, as did
the valleys of eastern Oregon and northern Nevada, where up to 2
inches accumulated. About 2 inches of snow were reported in
northeast Wisconsin, too.
   A storm spread rain in the Northwest, but it amounted to no more
than a quarter-inch across the region. In Illinois, scattered rain
fell early this morning after light rain late Monday in the western
Ohio and western Tennessee valleys.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers from western and
central New England to the upper Ohio Valley, and from there to the
southern Appalachians and parts of Alabama and Mississippi; snow
mixed with rain in upper Michigan; rain from the Pacific Northwest
to the northern and central Plateau region; and snow in parts of
Montana and Wyoming.
   High temperatures were predicted in the 40s in northern New
England, and from Michigan to the upper Mississippi Valley, North
Dakota and the northern Rockies, and eastern Washington state; 70s
from the Carolinas to the Gulf Coast and the southern Plains, and in
Southern California; 80s in Florida, southern Louisiana, much of
Texas and the desert Southwest; 50s and 60s in the rest of the
nation.
   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 22 degrees at
Custer, S.D., to 77 at the Naval Air Station near Corpus Christi,
Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 52 fair; Boston 42 fair; Buffalo 42 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 46 fair; Cincinnati 50 cloudy; Cleveland 41
showers; Detroit 40 rain; Miami 64 fair; New York 44 partly cloudy;
Philadelphia 41 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 36 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine 38 fair; Washington 41 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 32 fair; Chicago 39 foggy; Dallas-Fort Worth
53 fair; Denver 31 fair; Des Moines 33 fair; Indianapolis 49 fair;
Kansas City 36 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 37 cloudy; Nashville 63
cloudy; New Orleans 70 fair; St. Louis 41 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 49 fair; Anchorage 31 cloudy; Las Vegas 68
cloudy; Los Angeles 60 partly cloudy; Phoenix 69 partly cloudy; Salt
Lake City 44 cloudy; San Diego 61 cloudy; San Francisco 52 partly
cloudy; Seattle 44 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 39 cloudy; Toronto 41 cloudy.
</TEXT>
