<2ND_LINE>PM-Beating Death,0237</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Dies Of Beating After Buying Grandchildren Christmas Presents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman has died two days after she was
beaten by robbers trying to steal $11 she intended to use to buy
Christmas presents for her grandchildren.
   Shirley Lockett, 47, died Monday at University Hospital,
apparently from injuries she suffered Saturday in the attack in a
discount store parking lot, Jefferson County Deputy Coroner Stan
Pitts said.
   The coroner's office said the death is being treated as a
homicide. No one has been charged.
   Mrs. Lockett's oldest daughter, Marcella Agee, 26, said her
mother said she was attacked when she got out of her car. She said
two men tried to steal her purse, which contained the $11, and also
might have been after her Cadillac.
   ``She said she was getting out of her car when two men started
hitting her in the face with brass knuckles. She said that some
other people in the parking lot then chased the men off'' before
they got either the purse or car, Mrs. Agee said.
   Mrs. Lockett passed out after the attack, but regained
consciousness and drove five blocks to her home. Her family took her
to Cooper Green Hospital and she was transferred to University
Hospital because of the severity of her injuries, said University
spokesman Hank Black. She later lost consciousness at the hospital
and died.
