<1ST_LINE>r a PM-ChildDeath     11-08 0291</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Child Death,0299</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Child Dies From Gun Wound Allegedly Inflicted by Father</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-year-old girl has died four days after
she was shot in the head while her father held her and her sister
hostage, authorities said.
   Latasha Shoulders died Monday at the University of Mississippi
Medical Center of a gunshot wound to the head, Hinds County Coroner
Robert Martin said.
   Her 8-year-old sister, Dawn, died Thursday, the day of the
shootings, also of a shot to the head.
   ``You couldn't find any better kids,'' the girls' uncle, William
Harkless, said after learning of Latasha's death.
   The sisters were shot while their father, 37-year-old Emanuel
Shoulders Jr., allegedly held them hostage in the attic of Harkless'
Jackson home.
   Police had been attempting to serve Shoulders with an arrest
warrant accusing him of raping his 12-year-old stepdaughter. When
police arrived at Harkless' house, Shoulders refused to answer the
door.
   About an hour later, officers heard what they thought were shots
inside the house. Police went in and found the children with their
wounded father lying on top of them.
   Shoulders, believed to have shot himself in the head, has been in
critical condition at Hinds General Hospital. Hospital officials
would not release his condition Monday night.
   Shoulders' wife, Francis, had confronted him by telephone
Thursday morning with suspicions that he had sexually molested her
12-year-old daughter. She said she found a note written by Shoulders
in his wallet describing what he had done to the girl.
   After the conversation, Shoulders left his job and took the two
sisters out of Lake Elementary School. Mrs. Shoulders left her job
to get her 12-year-old out of school and went to police to file the
rape charge against her husband.
</TEXT>
