<HEAD>Former Managing Editor of Ottawa Journal Dead at 81</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OTTAWA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George J. Paterson, former managing editor of the
Ottawa Journal, has died at the age of 81.
   The native of Edinburgh, Scotland, who died Monday, came to
Ottawa in 1929 as an exchange reporter from the Edinburgh Tribune.
He originally intended to return after a year or two, but decided to
stay.
   A reporter during World War II, Paterson moved on to night
editor, news editor and finally managing editor. He retired in
November 1974.
   Services will be held Wednesday.
</TEXT>
