<1ST_LINE>r a AM-PoliceShooting     11-08 0249</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Police Shooting,0258</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Search Woods After Officer Is Gunned Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CONWAY, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police questioned one man Tuesday and
searched a heavily wooded area of Faulkner County for suspects in
the shooting death of a Conway policeman.
   Ray Noblitt, 42, of Vilonia, an 11-year veteran of the force, was
shot late Monday, authorities said.
   Police Chief Vonnie Taylor said Noblitt had stopped to
investigate a suspicious vehicle at Loveless Tractor Co. He said
someone apparently was trying to steal a trailer or a
tractor-trailer rig.
   After the shooting, the suspects fled north on a U.S. highway,
police said. The Faulkner County Sheriff's Department set up
roadblocks during the night on that highway and another road.
   ``We still don't know how many suspects that there are. We feel
there are more than one,'' said Conway officer Kerry Pool.
   Officials searched Tuesday near the community of Barney, about 15
miles northeast of Conway, which is about 20 miles north of Little
Rock.
   ``It's very rural. If you blink your eyes, you miss it. It's
heavily wooded,'' said Pool.
   The man in custody was questioned, ``but not necessarily in
connection with the shooting itself,'' Pool said. He declined to
name the man.
   Taylor said Noblitt was shot after he got out of his car.
   ``We believe he returned fire,'' the police chief said. ``We
haven't checked his weapon, so we're not sure.''
   Police were notified of the shooting when someone used the
officer's police radio to call the station.
</TEXT>
