71-year-old Cleveland millionaire said the race would be his last.
   Voinovich matched Metzenbaum in spending, but his campaign
nosedived after a television ad that sought to paint Metzenbaum as
soft on child pornographers. Newspapers statewide deplored the
tactic, and the Metzenbaum campaign answered with its own ad: a spot
in which fellow Democrat Sen. John Glenn called the Voinovich charge
``disgusting.''
