had 379,528 votes, or 33 percent.
   In the presidential race, Bush had 704,724 votes, or 59 percent,
to Dukakis' 484,294 votes, or 41 percent. The victory gave Bush 12
electoral votes.
   Indiana voters also repealed the state's 137-year-old
constitutional ban on lotteries.
   GOP Gov. Robert D. Orr was barred from seeking a third term.
   In House races, Indiana Democrats tried to protect their 6-4
advantage. Three Democrats and three Republican incumbents won
re-election in six districts. The other four races were inconclusive.
