<HEAD>Oil Futures Prices Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Energy futures prices have gained some ground,
with most of the buying interest was focused on unleaded gasoline.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the December contract for
unleaded gasoline gained 0.91 cent to settle Monday at 47.25 cents a
gallon, after rising 1.14 cents on Friday.
   Among other refined petroleum products traded on the exchange,
the December contract for wholesale home heating oil, which fell
0.24 cent on Friday, was up 0.05 cent to 44.13 cents a gallon.
   The December contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
U.S. crude, closed at $14.06 a barrel, up 2 cents. The contract
increased 14 cents on Friday.
   Most traders continued to take a low profile ahead of the next
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries meeting scheduled for
Nov. 21, analysts said. OPEC is likely to discuss cutting production
as a way of increasing sagging worldwide oil prices.
</TEXT>
